# Files excluded from the Docker build context.
#
# The Dockerfile's `COPY` directives pull in only what they need
# (package.jsons, source, lockfile). This list excludes everything
# that would otherwise bloat the context and slow down the build:
#
# - `node_modules` are excluded from the COPY layer and installed
#   inside the image via pnpm (so the host's platform-specific
#   binaries don't leak into a linux image).
# - `dist` is excluded because the image builds fresh from source.
# - `.git`, `.codegraph`, IDE files, etc. are noise.
# - `.env` is excluded so secrets never leak into the build context
#   (compose reads `.env` at runtime via `env_file`, not at build).
# - `coverage` and `tests` are CI-only artefacts.
# - `*.mmdb` is the MaxMind GeoLite2 binary — mounted at runtime
#   (compose), not baked into the image.
# - `openspec` and `docs` are SDD artefacts, not part of the
#   runtime / build.

# Dependencies
node_modules
**/node_modules
.pnpm-store

# Build outputs (the image builds fresh)
dist
**/dist
*.tsbuildinfo

# Environment + secrets
.env
.env.*
!.env.example

# VCS + tooling metadata
.git
.gitignore
.gitattributes
.codegraph
.idea
.vscode
.DS_Store
*.swp
*.swo

# Test artefacts
coverage
**/coverage
.nyc_output
**/.nyc_output
*.lcov

# Test source (not needed at runtime or build)
tests
**/tests
**/*.test.ts
**/*.test.tsx
e2e
**/e2e
**/*.e2e.spec.ts
**/*.spec.ts

# SDD artefacts (design, proposal, specs)
openspec
docs

# Documentation
README.md
LICENSE
CHANGELOG.md

# CI / CD
.github
.gitlab-ci.yml
.circleci
.travis.yml

# Husky + lint-staged (host-only)
.husky
.lintstagedrc.json
commitlint.config.js
.eslintrc.cjs
eslint.config.js
.prettierrc*
.prettierignore

# Logs
*.log
logs
**/logs
npm-debug.log*
yarn-debug.log*
yarn-error.log*
pnpm-debug.log*

# OS noise
Thumbs.db

# GeoIP (mounted at runtime, not baked in)
*.mmdb
geoip

# Docker meta (don't recurse)
Dockerfile
docker-compose*.yml
.dockerignore
